00:35:08.350 --> 00:35:09.390
LAMA TSOMO: OK.

00:35:09.390 --> 00:35:11.848
FEMALE SPEAKER: And one of the
first things we did together

00:35:11.848 --> 00:35:12.605
was just breathe.

00:35:12.605 --> 00:35:13.210
That's It.

00:35:13.210 --> 00:35:14.810
Just pause and breathe.

00:35:14.810 --> 00:35:19.540
And almost any time I do
this I think and realize

00:35:19.540 --> 00:35:21.540
how shallow my breath is.

00:35:21.540 --> 00:35:24.710
And it's even shallow
when I'm noticing it.

00:35:24.710 --> 00:35:27.170
So imagine when I'm
just at my computer

00:35:27.170 --> 00:35:29.890
or in a meeting how
shallow it must be.

00:35:29.890 --> 00:35:32.470
And we use such a small
percentage of our lungs.

00:35:32.470 --> 00:35:35.860
And I wish we all
could sit and meditate

00:35:35.860 --> 00:35:39.130
in the base of the Rocky
Mountains in Montana,

00:35:39.130 --> 00:35:43.500
but unfortunately we don't have
quite that Big Sky fresh air

00:35:43.500 --> 00:35:44.500
around here.

00:35:44.500 --> 00:35:47.007
So in atmospheres like
the Silicon Valley

00:35:47.007 --> 00:35:48.840
I'm sure we have beautiful
meditation rooms,

00:35:48.840 --> 00:35:52.220
but how do you remind
yourself, even when you're not

00:35:52.220 --> 00:35:53.992
meditating, to breathe?

00:35:53.992 --> 00:35:55.700
How do you just
incorporate that practice

00:35:55.700 --> 00:35:58.260
into your daily motions?

00:35:58.260 --> 00:36:02.900
LAMA TSOMO: Well, I am
addicted to my computer, too.

00:36:02.900 --> 00:36:05.815
And I'll forget I'm on
a mountain top and all

00:36:05.815 --> 00:36:07.690
of the glorious things,
and I'm sitting there

00:36:07.690 --> 00:36:11.190
staring at the computer for
hours and hours every day.

00:36:11.190 --> 00:36:13.800
I also am in a lot of meetings.

00:36:13.800 --> 00:36:17.120
So you forget where you
are, at that point, right?

00:36:17.120 --> 00:36:19.920
You're just paying
attention to the thing.

00:36:19.920 --> 00:36:24.530
So I have this program which
I don't remember the name of,

00:36:24.530 --> 00:36:26.660
but I bet there are
several of them.

00:36:26.660 --> 00:36:30.580
And it just flashes
on your screen.

00:36:30.580 --> 00:36:33.520
You can still see behind
it, and you can always

00:36:33.520 --> 00:36:36.550
click it to dismiss it
quickly if you want to,

00:36:36.550 --> 00:36:41.460
but it also is a moment to just
remind you to take a breath

00:36:41.460 --> 00:36:43.730
and actually rest
your-- resting your eyes

00:36:43.730 --> 00:36:46.220
and focusing them at
least 20 feet away

00:36:46.220 --> 00:36:48.490
is really good for your eyes.

00:36:48.490 --> 00:36:50.810
Keeps you from going
near-sighted, staring

00:36:50.810 --> 00:36:52.150
at a screen all the time.

00:36:52.150 --> 00:36:55.230
Your eyes aren't meant to
be focused on one distance

00:36:55.230 --> 00:36:56.520
all the time.

00:36:56.520 --> 00:36:58.630
So, for lots of
reasons, you can set it

00:36:58.630 --> 00:37:01.600
for however timing you want,
if you want it every hour,

00:37:01.600 --> 00:37:05.080
every half-hour, whatever it is.

00:37:05.080 --> 00:37:06.870
That's a simple reminder.

00:37:06.870 --> 00:37:11.950
Also, if you do happen to notice
that you're feeling anxious,

00:37:11.950 --> 00:37:16.540
it's impossible physiologically
to be as anxious if you

00:37:16.540 --> 00:37:19.470
take a big breath and exhale.

00:37:19.470 --> 00:37:24.550
So we automatically sigh
sometimes when we're anxious,

00:37:24.550 --> 00:37:28.410
and you could just do that
even when your body might not

00:37:28.410 --> 00:37:29.860
have automatically done it.

00:37:29.860 --> 00:37:32.450
But if you just know about
this, that's a moment

00:37:32.450 --> 00:37:34.840
you can take a big breath.

00:37:34.840 --> 00:37:37.777
And when you do meditate
you're not meant to, like,

00:37:37.777 --> 00:37:39.290
force big breaths.

00:37:39.290 --> 00:37:43.510
It's supposed to be
just quite natural.

00:37:43.510 --> 00:37:48.200
And I find I tend to
savor in between in-breath

00:37:48.200 --> 00:37:51.730
and out-breath, because
it's just so quiet

00:37:51.730 --> 00:37:53.960
and still for that moment.

00:37:53.960 --> 00:37:55.440
I kind of savor that.

00:37:55.440 --> 00:37:59.900
So that's what I
would say about that.

