00:38:09.062 --> 00:38:09.770
LAMA TSOMO: Yeah.

00:38:09.770 --> 00:38:14.620
So now we'll do a
more official guiding

00:38:14.620 --> 00:38:18.460
through the practice
of Samatha meditation.

00:38:18.460 --> 00:38:19.800
Shyine, in Tibetan.

00:38:19.800 --> 00:38:24.040
And Shyine means
"peaceful abiding."

00:38:24.040 --> 00:38:26.340
there are many different
kinds of meditation.

00:38:26.340 --> 00:38:28.900
Everybody thinks there's-- or,
most people think there's just

00:38:28.900 --> 00:38:32.900
one, but actually you can
come at this thing from many

00:38:32.900 --> 00:38:33.940
directions.

00:38:33.940 --> 00:38:35.840
Some are compassion
meditations, some

00:38:35.840 --> 00:38:41.790
are-- actually there some
very athletic ones further

00:38:41.790 --> 00:38:43.610
on down the road.

00:38:43.610 --> 00:38:50.820
And some that clear away the
first static that we feel

00:38:50.820 --> 00:38:52.790
when we sit down to meditate.

00:38:52.790 --> 00:38:56.140
But the one I'm going to
share with you is Samatha.

00:38:56.140 --> 00:38:58.120
So there isn't too much
more than I already

00:38:58.120 --> 00:38:59.585
told you, actually.

00:38:59.585 --> 00:39:02.610
It's very simple.

00:39:02.610 --> 00:39:06.220
That doesn't mean
easy, but simple.

00:39:06.220 --> 00:39:08.210
So one thing is posture.

00:39:08.210 --> 00:39:14.210
And this is going to help you
to achieve the clear yet calm

00:39:14.210 --> 00:39:16.110
state that we're going for.

00:39:16.110 --> 00:39:18.380
What we aren't going
for is agitated,

00:39:18.380 --> 00:39:20.790
nor are we going for sleepy.

00:39:20.790 --> 00:39:23.600
And I don't know about you, but
when I haven't had enough sleep

00:39:23.600 --> 00:39:27.030
and I drink too much coffee, I
can do both agitated and sleepy

00:39:27.030 --> 00:39:29.280
at same time.

00:39:29.280 --> 00:39:30.750
So we're not going for that.

00:39:30.750 --> 00:39:34.870
We're going for clear and calm.

00:39:34.870 --> 00:39:38.980
So there is an exercise for
that that only takes, like,

00:39:38.980 --> 00:39:40.740
30 to 60 seconds.

00:39:40.740 --> 00:39:43.430
It's in the book and there's
a demonstration of it

00:39:43.430 --> 00:39:47.187
because there are some
movements on our website.

00:39:47.187 --> 00:39:49.020
You can get to our
website from the handout.

00:39:51.580 --> 00:39:54.080
It's Namchak.org.

00:39:54.080 --> 00:40:00.250
N-A-M-C-H-A-K. Namchak.org.

00:40:00.250 --> 00:40:02.730
Because you'll need
to see a video of that

00:40:02.730 --> 00:40:04.140
to really be able to do it.

00:40:04.140 --> 00:40:06.900
But it kind of jump starts
your Samatha practice.

00:40:06.900 --> 00:40:08.510
So here's Samatha.

00:40:08.510 --> 00:40:10.820
You sit with your back straight.

00:40:10.820 --> 00:40:14.550
If you can do full Lotus
position, wonderful.

00:40:14.550 --> 00:40:15.420
Tell your friends.

00:40:15.420 --> 00:40:19.290
You should be proud you
can also sit cross-legged.

00:40:19.290 --> 00:40:20.920
You can sit on a chair.

00:40:20.920 --> 00:40:23.460
Any of that will do.

00:40:23.460 --> 00:40:25.480
The main thing is
that you're sitting

00:40:25.480 --> 00:40:29.130
with your hip joint bent.

00:40:29.130 --> 00:40:34.130
And there's-- you know,
what happens with the prana,

00:40:34.130 --> 00:40:37.790
the chi, is helped by that.

00:40:37.790 --> 00:40:40.380
And then you need your back
straight because again,

00:40:40.380 --> 00:40:46.620
your prana needs to flow
in a straight, open pathway

00:40:46.620 --> 00:40:49.300
up your spine.

00:40:49.300 --> 00:40:55.930
So you're sitting not
with a taut, rigid spine,

00:40:55.930 --> 00:40:58.470
but supple and straight.

00:40:58.470 --> 00:41:01.180
And it turns out that
hunching is actually

00:41:01.180 --> 00:41:05.930
straining some muscles
more than you realize.

00:41:05.930 --> 00:41:09.400
And a favorite thing is to
hunch and then have the head up,

00:41:09.400 --> 00:41:12.540
and then go visit the
chiropractor for your neck.

00:41:12.540 --> 00:41:16.100
So if you have your
vertebrae like a column,

00:41:16.100 --> 00:41:19.110
it's actually less
strain on everything.

00:41:19.110 --> 00:41:21.210
And you sit on your
sit bones, whether it's

00:41:21.210 --> 00:41:25.140
a chair or cross-legged
or whatever it is.

00:41:25.140 --> 00:41:28.090
If you are sitting on
the floor cross-legged,

00:41:28.090 --> 00:41:30.870
it's important to have a
little bit of elevation.

00:41:30.870 --> 00:41:36.880
Your rear needs to be on a
firm cushion and your knees

00:41:36.880 --> 00:41:39.150
a little bit lower, and
it just really helps

00:41:39.150 --> 00:41:44.610
to be able to sit straight
comfortably, very easily.

00:41:44.610 --> 00:41:45.650
So that's important.

00:41:45.650 --> 00:41:47.140
And the visualization
that I think

00:41:47.140 --> 00:41:50.440
helps for me is imagining
that, through the back top

00:41:50.440 --> 00:41:55.770
of my head, is a string that's
hanging from the ceiling.

00:41:55.770 --> 00:41:58.580
So I'm like this marionette.

00:41:58.580 --> 00:42:02.310
Very relaxed, very supple,
hanging from the ceiling.

00:42:05.910 --> 00:42:09.830
And in our tradition we don't
close the eyes all the way,

00:42:09.830 --> 00:42:13.590
we have them facing
down, sort of following

00:42:13.590 --> 00:42:14.970
the line of the nose down.

00:42:20.070 --> 00:42:21.950
And your mouth is
a little bit open.

00:42:21.950 --> 00:42:27.080
You're going to actually breathe
mostly through your mouth.

00:42:27.080 --> 00:42:29.080
The tip of your
tongue is touching

00:42:29.080 --> 00:42:32.364
where the upper palate meets
the teeth, the upper teeth.

00:42:36.270 --> 00:42:38.536
And once again, you just pay
attention to your breath.

00:42:51.740 --> 00:42:54.880
Again, it's the
direct experience

00:42:54.880 --> 00:43:03.140
of the movement of your belly or
the coolness across your mouth.

00:43:19.150 --> 00:43:23.017
Thoughts will come and
go, and we let them.

00:43:54.830 --> 00:43:59.380
You find you've been following
after a thought, good.

00:43:59.380 --> 00:44:05.650
That's more awareness than
maybe you've had in years.

00:44:05.650 --> 00:44:08.210
Noticing that.

00:44:08.210 --> 00:44:11.990
And doing that bicep
curl for the brain,

00:44:11.990 --> 00:44:15.065
bringing your mind
attention back to breath.

00:44:31.240 --> 00:44:32.300
And breathing naturally.

00:45:19.050 --> 00:45:21.820
That was a quick introduction.

00:45:24.670 --> 00:45:28.410
And I'd like to follow
through with more right now,

00:45:28.410 --> 00:45:32.420
so if anyone had
their devices on,

00:45:32.420 --> 00:45:33.810
I'd like you to turn it off.

00:45:33.810 --> 00:45:37.280
You won't need to
take any more notes.

00:45:37.280 --> 00:45:42.867
And I invite you to take a
few minutes of real vacation.

00:45:49.530 --> 00:45:53.260
So we'll do this
again, remembering

00:45:53.260 --> 00:45:55.540
the marionette posture.

00:46:00.150 --> 00:46:03.510
Eyes gazing down.

00:46:03.510 --> 00:46:05.990
Tip of the tongue
where the upper palate

00:46:05.990 --> 00:46:07.124
meets the upper teeth.

00:46:11.770 --> 00:46:14.434
And settling our
attention on breath.

00:47:45.600 --> 00:47:50.300
Again, if you've been following
after a thought, good.

00:47:50.300 --> 00:47:53.220
You noticed.

00:47:53.220 --> 00:47:59.125
Bring it back and settle
freshly back into Samatha.

00:48:51.082 --> 00:48:55.580
The more times you notice
you've been making movies

00:48:55.580 --> 00:49:02.820
in your mind, the more that
means you've been aware of it,

00:49:02.820 --> 00:49:05.890
and the more times you can
freshly come back to Samatha.

00:49:48.080 --> 00:49:52.920
If you find your
mind is too jumpy,

00:49:52.920 --> 00:49:54.607
try to bring your
gaze a bit lower.

00:49:58.060 --> 00:50:02.430
And if it's a bit sleepy,
raise your gaze just a bit.

00:51:03.980 --> 00:51:09.690
Now I'd like you to take
a moment and reflect.

00:51:09.690 --> 00:51:12.918
Ask yourself, how am
I feeling right now?

00:51:19.640 --> 00:51:21.170
Adjectives, perhaps.

00:51:21.170 --> 00:51:21.670
Images.

00:51:35.950 --> 00:51:42.970
Whatever this is that you're
feeling, hopefully good,

00:51:42.970 --> 00:51:46.980
I'd like you to savor it
for just a moment more

00:51:46.980 --> 00:51:50.150
as I ring the bell.

00:51:50.150 --> 00:51:53.875
And you listen to the sound
as it slowly fades away.

00:51:57.288 --> 00:52:00.276
[BELL RINGS]

00:52:43.110 --> 00:52:44.880
Thank you.

